EN:

>>>>>>YAHTZEE game rules:<<<<<<<

>>>Gameplay<<<
During a turn, a player may roll the dice up to three times.
On the first and second roll, they may set aside some dice and only reroll the others.
After the third roll, they must place their combination in one of the thirteen categories. This can also be done after the first or second roll.
Once a player has filled in a category, the next player takes their turn.
A player must fill in each category once during the game.
This means a player may score zero points in a particular category.
After players have filled in combinations in all categories, they tally their points.
The player with the highest number of points is the winner.

>>>There are two types of categories:<<<
Upper section: number combinations 1 through 6.
Lower section: poker-like combinations.

Combination      Points
Three of a kind  Total number of pips
Four of a kind   Total number of pips
Small straight   30
Large straight   40
Full House       25
Chance           Total number of pips
Yahtzee          50

A player can score a Yahtzee bonus if they have multiple instances of five of a kind in the same game.
The condition is that the first Yahtzee must be scored with 50 points and not 0. The bonus is 100 points for the second and each subsequent Yahtzee.

/////maybe add
The combination is also filled in another category during the same turn.
If the Yahtzee box has already been filled in (with 0 or 50 points), the combination also counts as three of a kind, Four of a kind,
Chance: totale_score of all five dice, Full House (25 points), Small straight (30 points), or Large straight (40 points).
The condition is that the box from the list 1 through 6 of the number of pips of the relevant Yahtzee has already been filled in.

/////minigame?
There are also five-round competitions,
where the player with the highest total points after five rounds is declared the overall winner.
The game can also be played solo. The player can then keep a list of high scores.


